SIMPLE: overcount
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: overcount
<hw>o`ver*count"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
rate too high.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To count erroneously, such that the counted number
is higher than the actual number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overcount</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: overcount
<hw>o`ver*count"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A count{1} that
is higher than the true number; an erroneously high number determined by
counting incorrectly; the result of overcounting{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overcover</ent>⟦br⟧
